					<description><![CDATA[<p>Robotics Funding Strengthens August Robotics Expansion Strategy August Robotics Raises $30M in Series B funding to accelerate its construction and industrial automation platform. The round was led by Big Pi</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/august-robotics-raises-30m-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal">August Robotics Raises $30M to Scale Construction Automation Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Robotics Funding Strengthens August Robotics Expansion Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">August Robotics Raises $30M in Series B funding to accelerate its construction and industrial automation platform. The round was led by Big Pi Ventures, with participation from Blackbird, Skip Capital, Tanarra, Future Family Office, and GS Futures. The company develops modular robotics systems designed to automate complex construction workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Hong Kong based company focuses on robotics for large scale industrial environments. Its systems are designed to reduce manual labour in construction projects. The platform enables autonomous execution of site tasks with real time coordination. This includes planning, localisation, and multi robot fleet orchestration.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2017 by Alex Wyatt, August Robotics builds infrastructure focused robotics systems. The company has developed an in-house autonomy stack. This system allows robots to interpret project plans and execute tasks independently. It also enables error detection and correction during operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will support expansion of operations and continued development of its robotics platform. The company aims to scale production across multiple global regions. It is also expanding its engineering and deployment capabilities.</span></p>
<h2><b>Construction Automation Demand Drives Robotics Adoption</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">August Robotics operates at the intersection of robotics and construction infrastructure. The company targets inefficiencies in large scale building projects. These inefficiencies often slow down critical developments such as data centre construction.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s systems are already deployed across hyperscale construction environments. These deployments span the United States and Europe. The robots are used in high precision drilling and floor marking operations. They are designed for repetitive and </span><a href="https://www.wisdomlib.org/concept/hazardous-tasks" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">hazardous tasks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Big Pi Ventures led the funding round. Partner Panos Metsis said construction timelines can be significantly reduced using robotics systems. He noted that automation can shorten data centre build times by more than three months. This highlights the growing importance of robotics in infrastructure development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors see strong potential in physical automation technologies. The construction sector remains highly labour intensive. Robotics offers a pathway to improve speed, precision, and safety. August Robotics is positioning itself within this transformation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company operates multiple product lines. Its Lionel system is used for floor marking in exhibitions and large indoor spaces. It has already marked more than 300 million square feet globally.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Driven Robotics Platform Expands Global Deployment</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_201634" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201634" class="size-full wp-image-201634" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/August-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI-driven construction robotics converting digital plans into automated workflows, showing autonomous drilling systems deployed across large infrastructure sites." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-201634" class="wp-caption-text">August Robotics is expanding its AI-driven construction robotics platform globally, enabling automated workflows, autonomous drilling systems, and large-scale infrastructure deployment supported by advanced AI and manufacturing capabilities. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">August Robotics has developed a modular robotics platform. The system ingests construction plans and converts them into automated workflows. It also coordinates fleets of robots operating simultaneously on large sites.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s newer product line focuses on autonomous drilling systems. These robots are designed for prefabricated construction environments. They are used primarily in data centre construction projects.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The drilling robots were launched in partnership with Stanley Black and Decker’s DEWALT brand. They are already deployed across hyperscale infrastructure sites. These deployments demonstrate the scalability of the platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Alex Wyatt said the system compresses construction timelines significantly. He noted that automation helps bring critical infrastructure online faster. The company aims to expand its robotics capabilities across more construction workflows. The Series B funding will support development of new robotic systems. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It will also strengthen AI capabilities within the platform. The company plans to scale manufacturing and increase global deployment capacity. August Robotics is also developing a new data and AI research centre. The facility will be located in Melbourne. It will support advanced robotics and machine learning development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/muybridge-raises-16m-ai-imaging-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Muybridge Raises $16M to Scale AI Imaging and Virtual Camera Technology</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Global Expansion Strategy and New Regional Hubs</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">August Robotics plans to expand its global footprint following the funding round. The company currently operates across seven hubs. These span the United States, Asia, Australia, and Europe.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A new regional hub will be established in Athens. This location will support operations across Europe, the Middle East, and Africa. The hub will handle deployment, maintenance, and customer support services. It will also support field engineering teams.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company selected Athens due to its engineering talent pool. It also benefits from its geographic position between Europe and the Middle East. This location supports faster regional deployment and customer engagement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Alex Wyatt said the company will continue expanding its global operations. He noted that the funding will support new robotic product development. These systems will target construction, exhibition, and industrial environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors highlighted the long term vision of the platform. Blackbird partner Rick Baker said the company has spent years building foundational robotics infrastructure. He emphasised the importance of sustained development in deep technology companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Big Pi Ventures said it will actively support August Robotics as it scales. The firm believes the company is addressing critical infrastructure bottlenecks. It sees robotics as a key driver of future construction efficiency.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/august-robotics-raises-30m-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal">August Robotics Raises $30M to Scale Construction Automation Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
